  "img": "https://assets.forge-vtt.com/bazaar/systems/dnd5e/assets/icons/spells/link-spirit-3.jpg",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>At 10th level, you gain the ability to consult with your ancestral spirits. When you do so, you cast the @Compendium[5e-complete.5e-spells.CCYKOHoTUKUAsFlK]{Augury} or @Compendium[5e-complete.5e-spells.iZKiEQoREfH20RVn]{Clairvoyance} spell, without using a spell slot or material components. Rather than creating a spherical sensor, this use of Clairvoyance invisibly summons one of your ancestral spirits to the chosen location. <strong>Wisdom </strong>is your spellcasting ability for these spells.</p>\n<p>After you cast either spell in this way, you can’t use this feature again until you finish a <strong>short </strong>or <strong>long rest</strong>.</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p><em> Note: After adding Augury and Clairvoyance to your character, set their Preparation Mode to Innate Spellcasting, with Resource Consumption set to Item Uses: Consult the Spirits.</em></p>\n</section>",
